	<div id="about">
		<h1>Tim Lum is a designer &amp entrepreneur at Pixel Flex.</h1>
		
		<p>At an early age I was fortunate to discover my passion for art &amp design. Exploring my creativity through many different mediums, I focused &amp honed my artistic strengths to the services I provide my clients today.</p>

		<p>I attended <a href="http://www.canadorec.on.ca/">Canadore College of Applied Arts</a>, graduating with a Diploma in Graphic Design Productions and a Certificate in Interactive Multimedia with academic honours. During my education I started my freelance business by participating in the Ministry of Economic Development &amp Trade Program, <a href="http://www.ontariocanada.com/ontcan/1medt/smallbiz/en/sb_ye_summerco_en.jsp">Summer Company</a>.</p>

		<p>After graduation I worked as a designer at Penney &amp Company and Axiom Audio where I learned valuable fundamentals in the industry. I gained a wealth of experience in print design, photography, and ecommerce before launching Pixel Flex on October 1st 2008.</p>

		<p>During my start-up phase I participated in the <a href="http://cybf.ca/">Canadian Youth Business Foundation</a> (CYBF), which supported my financing and mentoring by Jesse Bennett-Chamberlain, <a href="http://31three.com/">31Three</a>.</p>

		<p>I am currently a <a href="http://www.rgd.ca/">Registered Graphic Designer</a> at <a href="http://www.pixelflex.com/">Pixel Flex</a> with over 8 years of work experience and always interested in new projects anywhere around the world.</p>
		<p><span>Personal Page credit goes to <a href="http://nazhamid.com/">Naz Hamid</a> over at <a href="http://weightshift.com/">Weightshift</a>.<span></p>
		
